AT MID-POINT OF RWY WE CAME UPON A HERD OF DEER CROSSING RWY IN  SINGLE FILE & EXTENDED TO THE L & R AS FAR AS I COULD SEE. I  BRAKED MOD. HARD & THERE WAS AN IMPACT THAT ACTIVATED THE ELT &  SPUN THE A/C AROUND TO L. I REGAINED CONTROL & CONTD ROLLOUT. I  WARNED OTHER A/C IN AREA & REMOVED DEER FROM RWY.  A/C SUSTAINED  SIGNIFICANT DAMAGE TO L  WING & L MAIN GEAR DOOR. I LATER LEARNED  TAHT THE UNIV THAT OPERATED THE ARPT HAS PARTIALLY INSTALLED A  FENCE WHICH FUNNELS DEER SO THAT THEY CROSS AT THE MID-POINT OF  THE RWY. PILOT LISTED SEVERAL STEPS TO REDUCE RISK OF A DEER  STRIKE.  4 DEER HAD BEEN STRUCK IN PAST 2 YEARS.
